<H3> <TI>   Ex-Ibaraki Governor Pleads Innocent in Trial </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0102015694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0144 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0102015694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 1 KYODO -- Former Ibaraki Governor 
Fujio Takeuchi pleaded innocent Tuesday [1 February] to a 
prosecution charge that he received a 10 million yen bribe from 
the country's leading contractor, Shimizu Corp., in 1992 while 
he was in office. 
  Takeuchi, called to answer the charge at the Tokyo District 
Court, categorically denied receiving the money from Shimizu. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

