<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Announces Subsidies for 12 Industries </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3101080694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0727 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3101080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 31 KYODO -- The Labor Ministry said 
Monday [31 January] that 12 manufacturing industries, including 
bag makers, will be eligible for the government's employment 
adjustment subsidy for one year from Tuesday. Under the 
existing system, employers will be provided with a subsidy to 
pay a portion of salaries and allowances to employees who are 
temporarily laid off because of the economic slowdown. 
  The ministry said the 12 industries to be added to the list 
include offshore oil drilling, felt manufacturing, polyurethane 
making and processing, refrigerating and air conditioning 
regulators manufacturing and electric welding machine 
manufacturing. 
  Seventeen other industries, including piano and its 
accessories manufacturing, were also re-designated as eligible, 
the ministry said. 
  It said the list will cover 4,856,000 workers in a total of 
233 categories of manufacturers. 

</TEXT>

