<H3> <TI>   More Commentary on Stimulus Package Issue </TI></H3>
<H4>   Saito on Tax Cut, Hike Stance </H4>
<F P=102> OW3101105094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0950 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3101105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 31 KYODO -- Vice Finance Minister Jiro 
Saito hinted Monday [31 January] that his ministry may soften 
its stance on the issue of whether to deal together an income 
tax cut and a consumption tax hike. 
  "I have never explained the definition," Saito told a 
scheduled news conference. 
  He declined further comment, noting a joint economic forum 
of 
the government and ruling coalition parties was dealing with the 
tax issue. Saito said the ministry "will respect the decision 
made by the forum." 
  On the stock market that staged a sharp rally, Saito said 
there would be "no direct effects" on the state of the economy 
because market prices are determined by supply-demand conditions 
which do not necessarily reflect economic fundamentals. 

</TEXT>

