<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Commentary on Stimulus Package Issue </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kumagai Favors Tax Cut With Hike </H4>
<F P=102> OW0102034694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0328 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0102034694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 1 KYODO -- The government should 
propose an income tax cut in tandem with an increase in 
consumption tax, Hiroshi Kumagai, minister of international 
trade and industry, said Tuesday [1 February]. 
  Kumagai told reporters after a regular cabinet meeting that 
the combination of an income tax cut and a consumption tax hike 
has been the fundamental notion of Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa's cabinet. 
  "It is up to the government and the ruling parties to make 
adjustments for combining the tax cut and the tax hike," he said. 
  Asked about the scale of income tax reduction, Kumagai said 
the cut should help quicken Japan's economic recovery and 
contribute to the global economy. 

</TEXT>

