<H3> <TI>   International Telecommunication Regulations Eased </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3101092094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0902 GMT 31 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW3101092094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 31 KYODO -- The Ministry of Posts and 
Telecommunications said Monday [31] it has eased regulations in 
seven areas of international telecommunications service, 
including leased circuit and collect call services. 
  The ministry said its approval will no longer be needed for 
domestic common carriers to begin additional overseas leased 
circuit service or for providing collect call service for 
countries with which Japan has regular telephone link ups. 
  Notification of the new measures were made to three overseas 
telecommunications operators, KDD (Kokusai Denshin Denwa Co.), 
International Telecom Japan Inc. and International Digital 
Communications Inc. 

</TEXT>

