<H3> <TI>   Retail Rice Prices Rise 0.6-1.6 Percent in Dec </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2401113494 Tokyo KYODO in English 1053 GMT 24 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2401113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 24 KYODO -- Retail rice prices rose an 
average 0.6 percent to 1.6 percent in December, the Food Agency 
said Monday [24 January], citing its nationwide survey. 
  The agency said the price of top-grade glutinous rice gained 
39 yen to 6,323 yen per 10 kilograms, while that of the second 
highest- grade rice moved up 83 yen to 5,754 yen. 
  The price of middle-grade rice rose 8.3 yen to 5,379 yen per 
10 kilograms, the agency said. 
  In Kanagawa Prefecture, west of Tokyo, the price of the 
highest- grade rice climbed as much as 584 yen, or 10.9 percent, 
to 5,948 yen per 10 kilograms, the agency said. 

</TEXT>

