<H3> <TI>   Final Preparations for H-2 Rocket Launching </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3001015894 Tokyo NHK General Television Network in 
Japanese 1000 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW3001015894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NHK General Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from "NHK News 7" program] </F>
  [Text] The final countdown has started for liftoff of 
Japan's next-generation H-2 rocket at Tanegashima Space Center 
in Kagoshima Prefecture on 1 February. The rocket is 50 meters 
long and 4 meters in diameter. It is a purely Japanese-made, 
practical large-scale rocket. 
  It is capable of launching a satellite of up to two tons, 
which is four times as heavy as past Japanese rockets. If 
everything goes well, the H-2 rocket will lift off four days 
from now -- at 0700 on 1 February. 

</TEXT>

