Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In connection with the North Korean Foreign 
Ministry spokesman's statement on the warning of the withdrawal 
from the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty, a government official 
today issued a commentary revealing that the government expects 
the North Korean side to respond to the government's efforts to 
resolve nuclear issues through dialogue under close cooperation 
with the relevant countries, including the United States. 
  In particular, in connection with the issue concerning 
Patriot missiles which was mentioned in the North Korean Foreign 
Ministry spokesman's statement, the government revealed that 
because Patriot missiles are purely defensive weapons, the 
government's review [komto] of deploying Patriot missiles is 
only one of the efforts to improve the ROK-U.S. combined 
defensive posture and thus has nothing do with nuclear issues. 

