Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 29 (YONHAP) -- South Korean Foreign 
Minister Han Sung-chu says that the North Korean nuclear issue 
would be referred to the U.N. Security Council unless it is 
resolved by Feb. 21 when the International Atomic Energy Agency 
[IAEA] convenes a Board of Directors meeting. Han made the 
prediction in an interview with Japanese correspondents 
stationed in Seoul, the KYODO news service reported Thursday. 
  Han also explained that even if North Korea agrees to IAEA 
inspections of its nuclear facilities, the agency will now have 
to undertake much more thorough and additional inspections as 
continuity of nuclear safeguards in North Korea has already 
broken, KYODO said. 
  Han said he expects some kind of results will emerge from 
the 
IAEA-North Korean negotiations on the inspection within next 
week. Han added that they could be either positive or 
negotiative, KYODO said. 

