  [Text] Rev. Billy Graham of the United States left Beijing 
for Pyongyang on Thursday carrying with him a verbal message 
from U.S. President Bill Clinton to Kim Il-song, a government 
source said. 
  "We understand Clinton's message calls on North Korea to 
resolve the nuclear question at an early date," he said. 
  The source added that Rev. Graham will drop into Hong Kong 
after his visit to North Korea, where he will have a press 
