<H3> <TI>   Graham's Visit to DPRK Examined </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK3101092994 Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN in Korean 31 Jan 94 p 20 </F>
<F P=103> SK3101092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KYONGHYANG SINMUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Chong In-hwa in the "North Korean Newsletter" </F>
column: "Christianity in North Korea Is a Bait for Inducing 
Western Capital"] 
  [Excerpts] World-renowned evangelist Rev. Billy Graham is 
now visiting North Korea. As a result, Christianity in North 
Korea is now the focus of attention. 
  Rev. Billy Graham previously visited North Korea in 1992. 
This is his second visit. North Korean radio has reported that 
during his meeting with North Korean President Kim Il-song Rev. 
Billy Graham conveyed a verbal message from U.S. President 
Clinton. Rev. Graham reportedly will hold revival services at 
Pongsu Church or Chilkol Church (formerly Pansok Church). 
  North Korea invited Billy Graham to North Korea in order to 
induce money from Christian circles for the development of the 
Najin-Sonbong district and discuss the construction of a large 
church in the area. [passage omitted on the state of 
Christianity in North Korea] 
  Experts say that just like Billy Graham's visit, Christians' 
visits to North Korea -- which North Korea facilitates to 
improve relations between North Korea and the United States, 
overcome its economic difficulties, and induce Western capital 
-- will continue. 

</TEXT>

