<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soldiers Returned Through Panmunjom </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0102063194 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0600 GMT 1 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0102063194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two North Korean solders, who were found adrift on 
the West Sea near Paengnyong Island, were rescued by our Navy on 
27 January. These two North Korean solders were repatriated to 
North Korea through Panmunjom at 1500 [0600 GMT] on 1 February. 
The two North Korean soldiers are Private First Class Kim 
Chol-chin and Private Kim Kyong-chol of North Korea's People's 
Security Forces. They were being treated at the capital 
military hospital. The issue of their repatriation was carried 
out from a humanitarian point of view, following their desire to 
return to the North. 
  The National Defense Ministry had discussed this matter with 
the North Korean side through the Military Armistice Commission 
on 29 January. This is the first instance of repatriation of 
North Korean soldiers who are on active duty. 

</TEXT>

