<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Congratulates Hosokawa on Reform Victory </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901130494 Seoul YONHAP in English 1255 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 29 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
congratulated Japanese Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa on his 
victory in a parliamentary battle for political reforms in a 
telephone conversation on Saturday evening. Hosokawa said he 
was pleased with the passage at the 11th hour by the Diet 
(parliament) of a political reform bill that has caused two 
governments to fall in the past six years and put his coalition 
cabinet on the brink of collapse. 
  The bill has drawn the world's keen attention for its aim of 
reforming Japan's political system and its failure would damage 
Japan's image in the international community, he added. 
  Kim said he is expecting his visit to Japan in March to 
provide another opportunity for the two countries to increase 
bilateral relations and for "both of us to deepen our 
friendship," as their meetings in Kyongju and Seattle did. 
  Kim then called for close cooperation among South Korea, the 
United States and Japan in the effort to achieve peace in 
Northeast Asia and in the world as well, expressing hope that 
the U.S.-Japan summit slated for next month will be successful. 

</TEXT>

