<H3> <TI>   Agriculture Accord Reached With New South Wales </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901014394 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD in English 29 Jan 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901014394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Agricultural &amp; Fishery Marketing Corp. yesterday 
agreed with the Australian state of New South Wales to promote 
bilateral cooperation on trade of agricultural and fishery 
products between Korea and Australia, a corporation spokesman 
said. 
  For this, Sin Tae-chin, the corporation's president, signed 
a 
contract with Ian Causley, agriculture minister of the 
Australian state, to establish a collaboration body between food 
institutions of the two sides, he said. 
  Last year, meanwhile, the state-run corporation's exports of 
agricultural, livestock, forestry and fishery products rose 
sharply 124 percent to $305 million from a year earlier, 
according to the spokesman. 
  By field, shipments of agricultural and livestock products 
soared 148 percent to $101 million in 1993 from the year before, 
while exports of fishery products skyrocketed 212 percent to $92 
million, he said. 

</TEXT>

