<H3> <TI>   Export Contracts Signed on Agricultural Products </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2801081594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0639 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2801081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 28 (YONHAP) -- The Agricultural and 
Fishery Marketing Corp. (AFMC) signed export contracts for 
Korean farm products worth 2.57 million U.S. dollars at the 
Berlin International Farm Products Fair, which ended Jan. 23, 
an AFMC spokesman said Friday. 
  Fifteen Korean companies displayed 54 items at the fair, 
with 
the most popular being sweet rice drink, pumpkin soup, kimchi, 
odorless garlic and chicken soup with ginseng. Ginseng 
products, a main export item, were not displayed at the fair so 
the contracts were poor. AFMC will attend nine international 
farm products fairs this year, including the Berlin Fair, to 
make Korean products better known to the world. 

</TEXT>

