<H3> <TI>   Missions Designated Internationalization Hubs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2901021794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0148 GMT 29 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2901021794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Jan. 29 (YONHAP) -- The Foreign Ministry 
designated 15 overseas missions as diplomatic hubs for the 
country's efforts for internationalization, a senior ministry 
official said Saturday. 
  The fifteen are embassies in the United States, Japan, 
Germany, France, Britain, Italy, Canada, Australia, Switzerland, 
Austria, Belgium, Netherlands, Sweden, Hong Kong and Singapore. 
  The missions will take on the job of gathering information 
on 
high technology and high quality products and deliver them to 
Seoul, he said. 
  They will also collect, investigate and analyze information, 
laws and practices on environment protection and transportation 
and will report the results to Seoul. 
  The Foreign Ministry also is studying plans to form a 
large-scale inspection team with officials of related ministries 
and send it to foreign countries. 
  Meanwhile, the ministry will issue daily reports on 
international situation with assistance of the Institute of 
Foreign Affairs and National Security and will distribute them 
to related ministries. 

</TEXT>

