<H3> <TI>   Presidential Family's Assets Increase $2.5 Million </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0102015794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0125 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0102015794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 1 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam has 
registered his family's assets at 2.08 billion won (2.5 million 
U.S. dollars) this year, up 440.59 million won from last summer 
due mainly to the growth of his father's fishing business. 
Under the public servants' ethics law, government officials 
above the grade one level who are obliged to disclose assets had 
to report any change in their financial standing since 
registration last Aug. 12 by Monday. 
  Kim himself is worth 575 million won, up 15.21 million won 
from 560.29 million won last August, due to the accumulation of 
monthly savings of 3 million won. 
  His other assets include a 410-million-won house in 
Sangdo-tong, Seoul, and 150 million won worth of farmland in 
Koje, South Kyongsang Province. 
  Thanks to a bumper anchovy harvest, his father, Kim 
Hong-cho, 
increased his wealth by 425.38 million won, which he has 
deposited in three separate banks. 
  President Kim's wealth grew by 15.21 million won due to 
interest increases in his monthly savings while his father 
benefited from the fact that he can deposit all his earnings now 
that he no longer has to contribute to his son's political 
activities, according to Hong In-kil, senior presidential 
secretary for administrative affairs. 
  Another change in Kim's assets resulted from his second 
daughter-in-law's purchase of a used car for 6 million won last 
September. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

