<F P=103> SK2901020694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rep. Kim Chong-in, former senior presidential 
secretary for economic affairs, was freed from prison yesterday 
after the Seoul Appellate Court reduced his sentence to 
two-and-a-half years in prison with a four-year suspension of 
execution. He was fined 210 million won. 
  The Seoul District Court sentenced Kim to a five-year prison 
term. 
  The appellate court also released An Yong-mo, former 
president of the Tonghwa Bank, by giving him the same period 
prison term with a four-year suspension of execution. It fined 
An 80 million won. 

