<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mahathir on PBS Using `Sentiments' To Keep Power </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102073794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0102073794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir Mohamed has expressed regret 
over tendencies of the Sabah United Party, PBS, State Government 
to use sentiments to cover up economic and development problems 
in its bid to retain power in the state. He said PBS leaders 
were willing to do anything to ensure their continued 
administration in the state, including the use of sentiments and 
creating hatred toward the federal government. The prime 
minister was addressing a dinner function organized by the Sabah 
Bumiputera [Indigenous]-Chinese chambers of commerce and 
industry in Kota Kinabalu last night. 
  Datuk Sri Dr. Mahathir clarified that the political 
stability 
and peace was the main factor for the rapid economic development 
in the country, which is able to maintain a growth rate of eight 
percent for six consecutive years. However, according to him, 
this was the national average per se. States like Pahang, 
Johor, and Melaka have achieved a 13-percent growth rate, while 
Sabah has recorded the lowest growth rate -- just a mere four 
percent. The prime minister explained that the federal 
government has no ill intention toward the people of Sabah and 
the federal government will assist a state toward development 
for the benefit of all the people in that state. 

</TEXT>

