<H3> <TI>   Defense Official Denies Report on Nuclear Arms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0102043194 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 1 Feb 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0102043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 1 February Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] At a news conference on 31 January, Shigeru 
Hatakeyama, administrative vice-minister for the Defense Agency, 
commented on a British newspaper report claiming there is a 
possibility that Japan may acquire nuclear arms in the future. 
He denied the report unequivocally, saying: "That is quite out 
of the question; it is quite incomprehensible why there should 
have been such a report." 

</TEXT>

