  From the latter half of the 1980's, Japanese-owned 
enterprises have been introducing the newest technology to ASEAN 
countries as they set up their branch operations there. Thus, 
since 1990, we see the volume of re-imports from these countries 
in terms of the consumer electronics industry rapidly 
approaching the volume of re-imports from Asian NIE's. In 
looking for the factors behind this remarkable progress in ASEAN 
member-countries, we should point out that Japanese enterprises 
had to transfer their operations to Korea and the other newly 
industrialized economies of Asia gradually while, at the same 
time, adjusting their production process to existing local 
industries; in the ASEAN case, however, the entire process could 
be transferred from Japan in one piece, thus making it easier to 
introduce the latest technology more effectively (Tables 16 and 
17). 


