<H3> <TI>   Foreign Leaders Greet President Kim Il-song </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0102052594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0446 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0102052594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 1 (KCNA) -- Comrade Kim Il-song, 
general secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party 
of Korea and president of the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea, exchanged New Year's cards with foreign state and party 
leaders. 
  He exchanged New Year's cards with Glavkos Kliridhis, 
president of Cyprus; President Shankar Dayal Sharma and Prime 
Minister P.V. Narasimha Rao of India; Ali Kafi, chairman of the 
High State Committee of Algeria; Sanni Abacha, head of state and 
commander-in-chief of the Armed Forces of Nigeria; Nicephore 
Soglo, president of Benin; Ronald Venetiaan, president of 
Suriname; B. Yeltsin, president of Russian Federation; Otto 
Stich, president of Switzerland; Thomas Klestil, federal 
president of Austria; Nir Mal Sen, general secretary of the C.C. 
[Central Committee], the Workers and Peasants Socialist Party of 
Bangladesh; K.P. Silva, general secretary of the C.C., the Sri 
Lanka Communist Party; Iqbal Ahmed Khan, secretary-general of 
the Pakistan Muslim League; Khaled Bagdash, general secretary of 
the C.C., the Communist Party of Syria; Mamadou El Bechir 
Gologo, secretary general of the National Direction Committee of 
the Sudanese Union-African Democratic Rally in Mali; Jorge 
Ibanez Castro, first secretary of the C.C., the Bolivian 
Communist Party; Hardial Bains, national leader and first 
secretary of the Communist Party of Canada (Marxism-Leninism); 
Rene Mauge Mosquera, general secretary of the C.C., the 
Communist Party of Ecuador; Vassalo Anthony, general secretary 
of the C.C., the Communist Party of Malta; Alfred Sant, leader 
of the Malta Labour Party; Manuel Vargas Loureiro, chairman of 
the Democratic Renovation Party of Portugal; and Zbigniew 
Wiktor, chairman of the National Executive Committee of the 
Polish League of Communists "Proletariat". 
  He also received New Year's cards from Idris Deby, president 
and head of state of Chad; Mohammad Zahir Khan, chairman of the 
Bangladesh Nationalist Republican Party; and Peter Symon, 
general secretary of the C.C., the Socialist Party of Australia. 
  And he exchanged New Year greetings with Hungarian President 
Arpad Goncz. 

</TEXT>

