<H3> <TI>   Officials Attend Opening of Paektusan Games </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0202043194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0406 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0202043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- "Paektusan Prize" 
games opened at the Handball Gymnasium in Chongchun Street in 
Pyongyang Tuesday. 
  The annual games held around the holiday of February since 
1977 are one of the large-scale sports contests in the country. 
  The games are held in Pyongyang and local areas till the end 
of February. 
  The participants compete in scores of events including field 
and track, basketball, volleyball, table tennis, boxing, 
wrestling (free style and greco-roman style), judo, swimming, 
shooting and archery. 
  Secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of 
Korea Kim Chung-nin, Vice-Premier of the Administration Council 
Chang Chol and officials concerned attended the opening ceremony. 

