<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Production Upsurge in Various Domains Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0202114094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1040 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0202114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- A production upsurge 
has been reported from different domains of the national economy 
in Korea. 
  The Musan mining complex, a leading production base of iron 
headings, has lifted production to a high mark in February after 
topping the January plan. 
  The complex hit the January target of iron headings three 
days ahead of schedule. In the period, it removed overburden 
more than double the amount in the same period toward the end of 
last year and secured 1.2 million more tons of crude ore. 
  The Tokchon district coal mining complex surpassed the first 
day's quota by far entering the new month. The complex 
overfulfilled the plan for last month 2.4 percent in capital 
tunelling, 20.9 percent in preparatory tunelling and 1.2 percent 
in coal production. 
  The Sunchon district coal mining complex, the Pyongyang 
thermal power complex, the Nakwon machine complex, the combined 
general bureau of shoemaking industry and the Korea silk 
association are boosting production from the first day of 
February after surpassing their January targets. 
  The Pyongyang silk mill topped the January plan for silk 
yarn 
50 percent, strongly backing the silk textile producers in 
increasing production. 

</TEXT>

