<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Sees Romanian Delegation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0102145594 Hanoi VNA in English 1439 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0102145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA Feb.1 -- Deputy Prime Minister Nguyen 
Khanh received here this afternoon an economic delegation of the 
Romanian government led by Mr. Cristian Ioneseu, minister of 
trade and chairman of the Romania's Sub-Committee of the 
Romania-Vietnam Inter Governmental Commission for Economic, 
Scientific and Technological Cooperation, currently on a visit 
to Vietnam to attend the 14th session of the commission. 
Minister Cristian Ioneseu informed Deputy Prime Minister Khanh 
of the activities of the commission and the results and 
solutions of the problems put forth at the commission's meeting, 
thus pushing up the economic, scientific and technological 
cooperation between Vietnam and Romania. He expressed his hope 
that possibilities and potentials of each country would be a 
basis for new development of such relation in the interests of 
the two peoples. For his party, Deputy P.M. Khanh affirmed that 
the Vietnamese Government and people always attach great 
importance to the existing relations between Vietnam and 
Romania. He expressed his belief that the current meeting of 
the commission would actively contribute to the further 
development of the cooperation between the two countries. 

</TEXT>

