<H3> <TI>   LDP Adopts 15-Trillion-Yen Stimulus Package </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0202044294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0409 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0202044294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 2 KYODO -- The opposition Liberal 
Democratic Party [LDP] on Wednesday [2 February] adopted a 15 
trillion yen economic stimulus package for presentation to the 
coalition government of Prime Minister Morihiro Hosokawa, party 
officials said. They said LDP President Yohei Kono will meet 
with Hosokawa later Wednesday to ask his government to implement 
the eight-point package. 
  The package, adopted by the party's special panel to combat 
the recession, includes a proposal for an "early implementation 
of major income tax cuts," the officials said. 
  The proposal did not mention the size of income tax cuts, 
but 
Ryutaro Hashimoto, chairman of the party's Policy Affairs 
Research Council, told reporters it should be more than 5 
trillion yen. 
  The program also called for a substantial reduction or a 
two-year freeze of the land value tax and urged the 
reorganization of financial institutions to improve the nation's 
financial system. 

</TEXT>

