<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Nuclear Weapons Said `Deployed' in South </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0202105094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1036 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0202105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["United States, Nuclear Criminal on Korean Peninsula"--KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- The United States is 
the nuclear criminal on the Korean peninsula. 
  The nuclear problem on the Korean peninsula arose from the 
introduction of nuclear weapons into South Korea by the United 
States. 
  The United States had no sooner unilaterally scrapped 
subparagraph 13d of the Korean Armistice Agreement banning the 
introduction of combat equipment and supplies from outside Korea 
in June, 1957 than it officially declared through an 
announcement of the U.S. Army authorities that it would start 
arming the U.S. troops present in South Korea with nuclear 
weapons. Then it shipped 280 mm a-guns and Honest John nuclear 
missiles into South Korea in February 1958, and deployed them 
near Uijongbu close to the Military Demarcation Line. The U.S. 
imperialists have introduced over 1,000 pieces of nuclear 
weapons into South Korea in more than 30 years since then, 
turning South Korea into their biggest nuclear forward base in 
the Far East. 
  The density of U.S. nuclear weapon deployment in South Korea 
is one per 100 square kilometers, or quadruple that in the NATO 
nations. 
  The United States has not ceased provocative acts 
threatening 
the DPRK, wielding the large number of nuclear weapons in South 
Korea. 
  All types of nuclear-capable planes ranging from B-52 
nuclear 
strategic bomber to F-16 tactical nuclear bomber and nuclear 
weapons from intermediary-range Lance nuclear missile to back 
pack nuke of Green Beret commandoes are mobilized in the "Team 
Spirit" joint military exercise, a test nuclear war, against the 
DPRK annually staged in South Korea since 1976. Even E-4B, a 
nuclear war commanding plane is hurled into it. 
  The United States announced the "withdrawal" of nuclear 
weapons from South Korea at the end of 1991, yielding to the 
strong demand of the Korean people and the world progressive 
people for the denuclearisation of the Korean peninsula and 
withdrawal of U.S. nuclear weapons from South Korea. But it 
revealed for itself that its withdrawal of nuclear weapons was a 
lie by opposing a comprehensive inpsection of the U.S. nuclear 
weapons and nuclear bases in South Korea which was raised by the 
DPRK. 
  And the United States and the South Korean puppets spread 
the 
fiction of "suspected nuclear development by the North" in order 
to mislead public opinion. 
  The United States, not satisfied with the deployment of a 
large number of nuclear weapons in South Korea, is going to 
massively introduce sophisticated "Patriot" missiles into South 
Korea. And it openly declared that it would continue to stage 
other joint military exercises larger in scale, even if the 
"Team Spirit" were suspended, taking issue again with the 
fictitious "nuclear problem" of the DPRK. 
  As facts show, the outcries of the United States and the 
South Korean puppets over the non-existent "nuclear issue" of 
the North remind us of a thief crying "stop thief " 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-28023 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas022_c_94003" </HT>


