<F P=103> SK0202042894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Corporal Kim 
Chol-Chin and Private 1st Class Kim Kyong-chol of the Korean 
People's Security Forces, who had been kidnapped by the enemy 
while drifting in distress in the sea off the Tungsan Cape on 
the West Coast on January 26, came back to the socialist 
homeland through Panmunjom on February 1. 
  The South Korean puppets detained them, not sending them 
back 
to the North instantly, and tried to make them defect to South 
Korea by all sorts of appeasement and deception. They, however, 
could not break the revolutionary constancy and will of the 
a-match-for-a-hundred soldiers who have grown in the bosom of 
comrade supreme commander. 
  The South Korean puppets were compelled to send them back to 
the Northern half of the country by the stubborn protest of the 
detained soldiers and repeated demand of our side. 
  The soldiers were interviewed by reporters in our side's 
portion of Panmunjom. 
  They exposed the attempts of the South Korean puppets to 
induce them to defection. Saying that they could be embraced in 
the bosom of the socialist homeland as there was comrade supreme 
commander for them, they stated they would be loyal subjects and 
filial sons safeguarding comrade supreme commander as his rifles 
and shells. 

</TEXT>

