<H3> <TI>   South's Response to 31 Jan Statement Denounced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302002094 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1500 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0302002094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1500 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to a radio report from Seoul, Yi 
Yong-tok, the South Korean puppet minister of the National 
Unification Board, on 1 February made groundless, malicious 
gibberish on the threat to the United States, intimidation 
against the South, and so forth, pertaining to the 31 January 
statement of a DPRK Foreign Ministry spokesman. 
  We cannot but say this is indeed a brigandish sophism 
completely reversing black and white and is a brazen-faced act, 
same as a thief yelling, "Stop thief!" 
  As has already been known, the United States has completely 
reversed [wanjonhi twijibo opko] its promise made to us during 
the DPRK-U.S. contact and has urged acceptance of the demand for 
full-scope inspections put forward by International Atomic 
Energy Agency Secretariat. Moreover, by designating even the 
time limit, the United States made a final notice-like threat 
and menace [choehu tongchopchogin wihyopkwa hyoppak], stating 
that if the demand is not met, the third round of DPRK-U.S. 
talks will not be held and the road to sanctions will be 
advanced. 
  The United States and the South Korean puppet clique are 
scheming to stage by all means large-scale nuclear war 
exercises, including the Team Spirit joint military exercise, 
against our Republic, and are accelerating on a full scale the 
deployment of Patriot missiles to South Korea. 
  This clearly illustrates that the United States has no 
intent 
to resolve peacefully the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula, 
but is pursuing its aim to crush our Republic with strength. 

</TEXT>

