inveigle Russia into the complicated situation of the Korean 
peninsula." This is out of due concern. If Russia was embroiled 
into the situation of the Korean peninsula which has been 
brought to the brink of war by the reckless moves of the U.S. 
imperialists and their lackeys, the situation would be rendered 
all the more complicated. 
  Anybody must not do something obstructive to a fundamental 
solution to the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula and its 
peace and peaceful reunification, but do something benefitial to 
them. 
  The South Korean puppet clique is obviously scheming to 
label 
Russia as a war conspirator by inveigling it into the dangerous 
developments which may lead to a new war on the Korean peninsula. 
  It must give up reckless moves of war and confrontation 
aimed 
at slaying the fellow countrymen in the North with the backing 
of outside forces, and promptly stop fooling and doing harm to 
others. 

