<F P=102>  SK0302115494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1032 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, February 1 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] 
-- A meeting of chairmen of the metropolitan and prefectural 
offices of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan 
(Chongnyon) was held in Tokyo over January 27-28. 
  Yi Chin-kyu, first vice-chairman of the Central Standing 
Committee of Chongnyon, delivered a report, which was followed 
by speeches. 
  The speakers called for making a new advance in 
strengthening 
Chongnyon as a chuche-based organization of overseas Koreans 
united in one mind, true to the new year's teachings of the 
great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  They vowed to fully establish the chuche-based leadership 
system in Chongnyon by invigorating the movement for learning 
from the greatness of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
They also resolved to make Chongnyon a patriotic organization 
full of vitality with its roots struck deep among the 
compatriots by strengthening its branches and chapters, 
radically enhancing the role of organizations of various social 
strata and thus uniting a greater number of compatriots. 

</TEXT>

