Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Keiko Tsuwa, 
chairperson of the Japan Women's Council, in a letter of request 
to the prime minister on January 25, denounced it is an 
anachronistic act that the Japanese authorities charged a trade 
company with "suspected violation of Cocom [Coordinating 
