<F P=103> SK0302122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Chairman of the 
Workers' Party of Turkey Dogu Ferincek, when he received the 
chief of the Korean general mission in France on January 28, 
said that the Workers' Party [WPK] of Korea was victoriously 
advancing socialist construction, pushing aside all machinations 
of the imperialists because it has achieved the singlehearted 
unity of the leader, the party and the masses under the wise 
guidance of the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song and the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  "Loyalty to the socialist cause and resolute 
anti-imperialist 
position maintained by the WPK gives a great encouragement to 
the communists of the world who are struggling for socialism," 
he stressed, and went on: 
  "The Workers' Party of Turkey [WPT] deems it great happiness 
to have friendly relations with the powerful WPK, greatest in 
the world. It will actively strive to learn from the idea and 
theory of Comrade Kim Il-song and Comrade Kim Chong-il on 
revolutionary party building." 
  He said he regards it as the revolutionary duty of the WPT 
to 
support the struggle of the Korean people for the independent 
and peaceful reunification of the country. He declared his 
party would conduct a powerful solidarity movement for 
supporting the struggle of the Korean people to achieve the 
reunification of the country in the 1990s in accordance with the 
ten-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation for 
the country's reunification advanced by the great leader Comrade 
Kim Il-song. 

</TEXT>

