<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Jose Fanequico, 
executive secretary of the Mozambican Committee for Friendship 
with the People of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea 
issued a statement to the press on January 21 under the title 
"Chuche Idea is Greatest Idea Based on Philosophical Principle 
That Man is Master of Everything and Decides Everything". 
  Noting that Comrade Kim Il-song, the respected leader of the 
Korean people, has put forward the greatest anthropocentric idea 
that guarantees human emancipation and boundless happiness for 
the people, he said this is no other than the great immortal 
chuche idea. 
  "The dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il is further developing 
and enriching the chuche idea," he said, and continued: 
  "The imperialists are most afraid of the truth that man is 
master of everything and decides everything, because they 
consider the popular masses their slaves and the target of 
exploitation. 
  "The imperialists are now most afraid of Korean-style 
socialism with the chuche idea as a guideline and the 
singlehearted unity of Korea. 
  "Genuine popular politics cannot be administered where there 
is no such a great anthropocentric idea as the chuche idea." 
Pointing out that "the chuche idea brings eternal freedom and 
happiness to the mankind, he stressed this is proved by the 
realities of Korea." 

</TEXT>

