<H3> <TI>   Cuban Lawyer Praises Kim Il-song, Country </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302114994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1011 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["`Comrade Kim Il-song, Great Man With Warm Humanity'" -- </F>
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Cuban lawyer 
Candelaria Rodriguez, who had visited Korea, said in a press 
interview in Havana on January 28 that Comrade Kim Il-song is a 
great man with humble, simple and warm humanity; 
  She was sent to Korea as a Cuban delegate of the 
fact-finding 
team of the Women's International Democratic Federation to 
investigate into the atrocities and crimes committed by the U.S. 
imperialists against the innocent Korean people during the 
period of the Korean War (June, 1950 - July, 1953). 
  She, who visited Korea in 1963 and 1993, expressed her 
impressions: 
  What astonished me greatly during my visit was that 
wonderful 
and great monumental edifices and modern streets such as 
Kwangbok Street, Tongil Street and Changgwang Street had been 
built like a forest in a matter of a few years. Pyongyang has 
been turned into a city of world level with 30-40-storeyed 
buildings. 
  The food, clothing and housing questions have been 
completely 
solved in Korea. 
  It is a beautiful trait that everybody lives evenly and 
equally in harmony, helping and leading each other forward. 
  The Korean art has combined what is traditional with what is 
modern. 
  The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song praised me as a 
comrade-in-arms of the Korean people and a revolutionary fighter 
when he received me. This cannot but be a great honor to me, an 
ordinary woman of Cuba. 
  Referring to the question of Korea's reunification, she 
said: 
  The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song put forward the 
"10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation for 
the reunification of the country" that is acceptable to all 
Koreans in the North and the South and overseas. 
  I am not a politician but I believe that Korea will 
certainly 
be reunified in the 90s. 
  The reunification of Korea is a long-cherished desire of the 
entire Korean people. 
  Comrade Kim Il-song and Comrade Fidel Castro are the 
outstanding leaders of the world and socialism is sure to win 
as long as it is led by the two leaders. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il is the successor to the revolutionary 
cause of Comrade Kim Il-song. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

