Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- Letters to the great 
leader President Kim Il-song were adopted at a meeting and joint 
seminars on his New Year address held in Georgetown, Guyana, 
Harare, Zimbabwe and Lima, Peru. 
  The letters say that the proposal to realise the 
reunification of the country in the form of confederation based 
on one nation, one state, two systems and two governments put 
forward by President Kim Il-song in his New Year address is the 
most realistic and fair one suitable to the conditions of Korea. 
  They express firm solidarity with the Korean people in their 
just struggle to resolve the nuclear issue of the Korean 
peninsula through dialogue and negotiation. 
  They promise strengthened support and solidarity for the 
struggle of the Korean people for national reunification this 
year and wish President Kim Il-song good health and long life 
for the victory of the socialist cause and a world-wide victory 
of the cause of independence. 

