<H3> <TI>   Visits to Kim Chong-il's Birthplace Increasing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0202144394 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1200 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0202144394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1200 GMT 1 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As the meaningful February holiday approaches, our 
people's heart running toward the revolutionary holy place where 
General Kim Chong-il, an ever-victorious and iron-willed 
brilliant commander, was born is all the more palpitating. 
  The number of observers and visitors who come to see the old 
home of the secret camp of Mt. Paetu with the heart of boundless 
thanks to and admiration for Supreme Commander Comrade Kim 
Chong-il, who defends the destiny of the fatherland and nation, 
leads the chuche-oriented socialist cause of our own style to 
the brilliant victory, and invariably leads the van of the 
revolution by going through violent storms, is increasing day by 
day. 
  According to the data compiled, the number of observers and 
visitors who toured the old home of the secret camp of Mt. 
Paetu, the revolutionary holy place, ran up to approximately 1.7 
million by the end of last year since its opening. 
  On the occasion of the auspicious February holiday, the 
number of observers and visitors touring the old home of the 
secret camp of Mt. Paektu is sharply increasing. 

