<H3> <TI>   Military Rebels Seek Releases Before Talks Resume </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0302092194 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0302092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tagalog </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The peace talks between the government and the 
RAM/SFP/YOU [Reform the Armed Forces Movement/Soldiers of the 
Filipino People/Young Officers Union] will continue to be 
suspended unless six of its detained members are released. This 
was revealed by RAM/SFP/YOU spokesman General Edgardo Abenina. 
Abenina said that the continued detention of its members is a 
violation of the agreement made between his group and the 
government last 22 December 1992. The agreement states that all 
members of RAM/SFP/YOU will be freed temporarily while their 
cases are still being heard. Abenina, however, expressed hope 
that the government is sincere in its peace initiative. Abenina 
added that the government is not clear on the procedures it is 
implementing for the peace talks. 

</TEXT>

