<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Reportedly Rejects Nuclear Inspections </TI></H3>
<H4>   IAEA Denies DPRK Rejection </H4>
<F P=102> SK0302120394 Seoul YONHAP in English 1157 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Berlin, Feb. 3 (YONHAP) -- The International Atomic 
Energy Agency (IAEA) on Thursday denied the press reports that 
North Korea had informed the IAEA of its rejection of any 
nuclear inspection. IAEA spokesman Hans Meyer said his agency 
had received no official notification from North Korea on 
Pyongyang's reported rejection of IAEA inspection of their 
nuclear facilities. Some press reports indicated that North 
Korea formally informed the IAEA on Feb. 2 that they were 
rejecting IAEA inspection. 
  Meyer said that the North Korean Embassy in Vienna 
fascimiled 
to the IAEA on Feb. 2 a copy of their Foreign Ministry 
statement of Feb. 1 on the issue of nuclear talks with the 
United States. But, this was part of their routine information 
activities, not any formal message to the IAEA on their 
rejection of nuclear inspection, he said. 
  The facsimiled item did not contain anything other than the 
three-page full text of Pyongyang's Foreign Ministry statement 
as reported by the North KOREAN CENTRAL NEWS AGENCY, Meyer added. 

</TEXT>

