<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Graham To Deliver Kim Il-song Message to Clinton </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302070194 Seoul YONHAP in English 0627 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302070194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, Feb. 3 (YONHAP) -- American evangelist 
Billy Graham said Thursday that a secret message from North 
Korean leader Kim Il-song will reach U.S. President Bill 
Clinton on Friday. Graham, fresh from a visit to Pyongyang from 
Jan. 27 to Feb. 1, said the message was being delivered to 
Clinton by a church associate at a press conference in Hong Kong. 
  The evangelist said he sent the associate to Washington 
ahead 
of him so that Clinton can receive the message by Friday, 
showing the urgency he attached to Kim's message. Graham said 
it was in reply to an oral message from Clinton which he had 
passed on to North Korea's paramount leader, but declined to say 
whether Kim's was oral or in writing. The renowned preacher 
said he spent more than three hours with Kim and talked about 
issues ranging from religion to politics, hinting that Clinton 
had touched on the North Korean nuclear issue in his oral 
message. He did not, however, elaborate on the content of the 
messages, nor that of his talks with Kim. He said he had 
discussed his planned visit to the Stalinist country earlier 
with Clinton, who strongly backed the idea. 

</TEXT>

