<H3> <TI>   Underground Student Group in North Uncovered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302124694 Seoul KBS-1 Television Network in Korean 1207 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0302124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a dispatch from Beijing, YONHAP reported on 3 
February that an anti-establishment underground student movement 
organization based on Kim Il-song University was carrying out 
activities in early 1992, but that it was uncovered by the North 
Korean authorities. Quoting its own source, YONHAP reported 
that the anti-establishment underground movement operated 
secretly from late 1991, mainly with students from the Kim 
Il-song University, but that the North Korean university 
students who took part in the underground organization were 
arrested by the authorities because moves by Chinese students 
studying in the North, who were part of the organization, were 
exposed by the Chinese Embassy in Pyongyang in early 1992. 

</TEXT>

