<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Officer Said Involved in Russian Sub Deal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302013294 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0005 GMT 3 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK0302013294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Korean </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Yi Il-hwa from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] Japan's TOKYO SHIMBUN reports that a North Korean 
high-ranking naval officer was involved in the DPRK's purchase 
of submarines from Russia. Accordingly, there is doubt whether 
North Korea will really use them as scrap material. North Korea 
had said some time ago that it was importing used submarines 
from Russia to use as scrap metal. The paper reported today 
that the Russian submarines which will be exported to North 
Korea (?are anchored) at (?Novik) Bay in Vladivostok, and that a 
North Korean high-ranking naval officer was involved in 
negotiations between North Korea and Russia regarding submarine 
transactions. The paper also reported that because of the North 
Korean naval officer's participation in negotiations on 
submarine transactions, there are doubts whether North Korea 
will really use them as scrap metal as it stated. 

</TEXT>

