<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier Orders Punishment of All Demonstrators </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302033194 Seoul YONHAP in English 0246 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302033194 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 3 (YONHAP) -- Prime Minister Yi 
Hoe-chang, deploring the violent farmer-student demonstration 
against rice market opening in Seoul on Tuesday afternoon, has 
ordered that all of those who broke the law be punished. 
  Presiding over a cabinet meeting on Thursday morning, Yi 
said 
street violence should not be allowed to occur again, noting 
some 300 people were injured in Tuesday's demonstration, his 
Press Secretary Kang Hyong-sok said. He also instructed that 
strict controls be imposed on elections for farm, livestock and 
fisheries cooperatives, saying they have already shown signs of 
corruption and rigging. 
  Yi told Economic Planning Minister Chong Chae-sok to pay 
special attention to price movements so that prices do not rise 
before Lunar New Year next week, while instructing Labor 
Minister Nam Chae-hui to see that workers' wages are not held in 
arrears during the holiday. He also stressed the need to ensure 
safe land and coastal transportation during the holiday. 

</TEXT>

