<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   President on Importance of International Trade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302125894 Seoul YONHAP in English 1126 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 3 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
stressed on Thursday Korean overseas missions should now be the 
center of market exploration and collection of trade and 
technical information. 
  At a Chongwadae [presidential residence] dinner he hosted 
for 
overseas mission chiefs and their spouses, Kim said the 
organization and function of overseas missions should change for 
the sake of new diplomacy. 
  "You should do actively anything that can be of help to 
strengthening the country's competitiveness," the president said. 
  Stating he is planning to have summit meetings with the 
leaders of major countries and would attend an APEC 
(Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation) summit meeting taking place 
in November in Indonesia, President Kim asked the senior 
diplomats to try to ensure national interests solidly in the 
course of preparing these and other events. 
  Korean mission chiefs posted in the American and Asian areas 
are now visiting the home country to attend an annual mission 
chiefs meeting. 

</TEXT>

