<H3> <TI>   Trade Association Elects New Chairman 3 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0302032494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0056 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0302032494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, Feb. 3 (YONHAP) -- Ku Pyong-hoe, chairman of 
Lucky-Goldstar International Group, was elected chairman of the 
Korea Foreign Trade Association (KFTA) Thursday in a general 
meeting of member companies held at the Korea Exhibition Center. 
More than 500 representatives of the companies also elected Pak 
Yong-hak, former chairman of KFTA, as honorary chairman. 
  Ku, the 22nd chairman of KFTA, said in his inaugural address 
that in view of the current trend of internationalization and 
economic opening, South Korea faces a critical moment on the 
road to becoming an advanced country. 
  "KFTA will strengthen information and other services for 
member companies as well as maintaining close cooperation with 
the government, thus playing a leading role in realizing the 
internationalization of South Korean businesses," he said. 

