<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Send Fire Victim Aid to Burma </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0302065394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0559 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0302065394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 3 KYODO -- Japan will send 8.77 million 
yen worth of emergency relief materials to Myanmar [Burma] for 
the victims of a large fire in Yangon [Rangoon] last month, the 
Foreign Ministry said Thursday [3 February]. 
  The government will send the goods, which include blankets, 
sleeping mats and soap, through the Japan International 
Cooperation Agency (JICA), at the request of the Myanmar 
government, the ministry said. 
  A large fire broke out in Yangon on January 24, burning more 
than 900 houses and affecting over 6,530 people, it said. 

</TEXT>

